values:
I return!!!!

Well I hope all has been well with everyone. I've been alright ^-^

So what you've missed:
 my brother had a kid with Sara who turned out to be a bit of a loon when she decided to run away from a perfectly good place here and then had the kid and hasn't (to this day) let my brother see her. My brother met another girl and married her last year. She's a beautiful girl named Columbia :D I love her, I'm glad she's my sister-in-law. ^-^

Bri, Rachael and I went to Hawaii in August of 07 with my mom and grandma; we had a blast. Still developing comics titled "the Hawaii Chronicles" :D

Dan and I started dating and things are going great, we're actually engaged now :D

As a family, in the summer of 09, my dad, mom, brother, sisters, brother-in-law, 7 grandkids, Columbia, Dan and I went to Florida and the Caribbean on a Disney cruise! It was awesome! We were at Disneyland for 4 days and stayed at the Grand Floridian hotel!! it was so beautiful and nice there. We could see the fireworks show and everything from our room. It was ridiculously humid there, but otherwise a very enjoyable experience. Malachi and Columbia got engaged on the beach in the Bahamas and then got married in March. If anyone is debating on taking a cruise at all, I highly suggest the Disney Cruise Line. Totally awesome.

Dan proposed to me on my birthday 2010, some "law- abiding-neighbor" set off illegal fireworks at just the right time to make it awesome for us :D

I finished Drama school at SDCCD and have taken a year off of school to try and find some acting jobs... needless to say, it's been rough.

Dan and I (along with family and friends) are planning for a December wedding at Disneyland in CA. It's gonna be awesome :D

Stay tuned for more, because this year is definitely gonna be one for the books >w< So exciting!

I suppose I'll just begin.... at the beginning

things have rather changed lately O.o... I'm sure its for the better, but I suppose now it'll be a bit harder.
My brother's coming home today with his girlfriend, Sarah.

If you don't know I'm speaking about my brother...I love him dearly but he's gotten himself into way deep water and now it's gonna be difficult to get back to a place where he can touch the bottom. If any of you pray... pray for them now. I'll spill more information as I deal with it.

anyways... Life is pretty much life going smoothly and everything. Went to the fair last week...and that was loads of fun, but only because we were all such goofballs >w< Bri-bear screamed on the crazy mouse ride and Dan and I couldn't stop laughing... seriously the constant screaming made us laugh and by the end of the ride my stomach was in so much pain. We bought the picture XD I also introduced Dan to the pearl game... or whatever its called where you pick an oyster and you get a pearl... because he never knew that existed and amazingly got twins (two pearls in one oyster) on his very first try!
so yeah we all had lotsa fun... oh! we also shot stuff and went into fun houses >w<

anyways not much has been happening for me, sytill looking for a job and all but otherwise I've just been writing stories and looking up names for characters.

well that's all for now...

ja mata!

Well I've been busy... and now I'm not. Now I'm bored and broke... I need a job... but no one seems to want to hire me... which really sucks *sigh*
well the past three weeks have been a blast :D
mostly >w<
I had a lot of fun the first week that school was out. We did like nothing XD it was great >w<
And then my Uncle, his GF and my cousin and his girlfriend Ana came... and I played chauffeur for an entire week.
It wasn't too bad... the first day I took them to the mall... my brother drove too... that was annoying. (great amount of irritation). I love my brother be he's such a pain because he never treats me with any respect and I have this distinct feeling that he hates that I'm smarter than him....
anyways... so that was fine.. after the mall we went to CPK for dinner, Dan came too. we all had fun and the Pizza was so yummy!!
Friday we went to the beach!!! whooo beach!!! that was so fun, but the water was so cold Adrian (my cousin) and Anna had a lot of fun. Anna had never been to the beach before so it was a real treat for her ^_^ Dan met us at the beach and pretty much ran into the water with the boogie board. Dan had just agreed to teach Adrian how to boogie board, but he'd stopped in his tracks when Dan ran into the water and asked "do I have to do that?" I responded with a no... he's just a lil crazy about the ocean. After the boogie board lessons Dan nearly dunked me in the water... since I'd not been completely in the water yet.... it was cold and I knew it was coming there was nothing I could do to stop it >.<

Saturday we went to the zoo! whooo! we left at like 11..... and then had breakfast/lunch so we actually got to the Zoo at 2:30... there was a lot of people since it was a Saturday, but all in all it was a lot of fun. When we went home we relaxed and plyed video games that Dan brought over with his X-box... so much fun >w<

Sunday was church *nod* we all had fun actually. And then we went to Ralph's to pick up some more steaks and stuff for the bbq! We also annoyed Dan and Bri who work at Ralph's >w< that was fun >w<
The BBQ was fun and yummy and no one sang or pulled out a guitar...so that was great.
Dan was there too and was getting picked on by the family, which was hilarious >w<
My brother was there.... with his new girlfriend Sarah (we won't get into the interesting details about how long they'd been together) and another friend of theirs who was there to help Malachi move out to Arizona that afternoon with Sarah...
So my bro's been in Arizona for the past month, he's coming out this weekend for a baseball tryout... it's weird but not...

Monday was a quiet mall day and we all had fun*nod*

Tuesday!!!!!! We went to Universal studios!!! hahaha!! that was so much fun. Bri and Dan went with me, my uncle, his GF Jenny, my cousin Adrian and Anna. ^-^ Bri and Anna had never been to Universal Studios and so we all had a blast. and I figured out the I get cranky and tired when I haven't had enough to eat *nod* ... so did everyone else.>.o
we managed to get Bri to go on The Jurassic Park river adventure ride...and that my friends was AWESOME XD
Initially Dan and I had told her that there was only a little drop and it was just a calm lil boat ride and it would be fun ^-^ So she went without a worry and yelled at the dinosaurs who got her hair wet throughout the ride... it was great XD
and then the finally came.... the final huge drop escaping the T-rex and the raptors into the water below....
she screamed and I couldn't stop laughing... here is the result.

Bri and Dan look Hilarious >w< My Aunt Jenny looks so scared too XD and you can't see me because my cousin decided to put his hand up covering my entire face *pout* all in all the whole trip was a success >w<
oh yes, did I mention I had to drive a whale boat? yes a whale boat, that is what the dodge caravan thingy was dubbed at the beginning of our trip. We wouldn't all fit in one of our cars so to save on gas we ended up renting a mini-van. *nodnod*

Anyways it was a whole lot of fun and a great end to my family's trip to California. ^-^
Oh yeah Bri, Dan and me all got characictures of ourselves...I forced Dan, and that was fun, but it didn't fit into my scanner so you don't get to see it.

After that things went by slowly... and we really haven't done much since. I've been on the job hunt...and so far I've come up empty...and I really miss Drama.... T-T

anyways I gotta go now since I have to vacuum the house and then shower before going to the beach.....as has been decided by the boy (aka Dan).

ja mata!

in the woods! XD

muwahahaha!! I'm finally out of classes!
Finals were intense!! I'm so glad the semester is over... well save for drama... I will surely miss drama... I think I'll join the major because I had so much fun >w<
    I will not miss Trig... I'll be happy if I pass the stupid class... my prof was a nazi.... hate *hiss* You know he actually showed up late for the final; giving me LESS time to complete it... and no, I did not finish the final... I almost did... but I was a few problems short *eye twitch*
So that was irritating.
English was a breeze, but I like writing so it was an easy class for me. Poli sci was fine, I studied and I'm sure I passed the class with an A or at least  B. Architecture... well drafting the final was 13 pages of answer questions and then like 5 pages or actual drawing... the final lasted 3 hours... the en tire class... I think I missed 3-4 questions. But I can safely say that I am so happy that class is over. I hated that prof too... nasty woman was so friggin' picky about every damn thing... one day I wanted to stab her eyes out... another day I wanted to slit her throat with my architect's scale... which is rather blunt and would have been messy... so I kept the violence in my head where it belongs.
Drama... oh drama... I seriously miss the class. I think it was the only class I looked forward to and actually put heart felt effort into it. I love acting ...working with people who also love acting. My last scene partner was the best.
 Ricky, I got to work with him twice because, for the final, we were short a few people and I was left without a scene partner. So he graciously allowed me to double up with him and Silver (one of my previous scene partners). We did a scene from The Woods by David Mamet, and it was awesome. Everyone saw a completely different side of me and I blew them all away >w< In all my previous scenes I'd been this sadistic, controlling, violent bitch so it was nice that in this scene I got to show something else that most people rarely get the chance to see (happy, loving, teasing and bubbly)... and I was real.
Anyways I had a blast and I'm definitely going back next semester, heck I might even join the major >w<

After classes were over we all celebrated with sushi!!! >w< home-made of course, by me :D we had fun and ate... a lot >w<and now I forgot what I was going to say because the stupid picture isn't working.... *stare*
anyways I might actually get a job this summer. I'll be working at Visual Photography, if I get the job, which I think I might, so that'll be cool :D making money is always good *sage nod*
I also hope to take a lot of pictures and have wonderfully funny, misadventures with my friends this summer >w<
<3 you guys!

and well that's all for now... I gotta figure out what's happening tonight and then I'm off to do stuff :D

ok so its a big deal. I'm bored and no one is here to distract me... no one is here for me to ignore T-T
I need a better distraction than my tv!!!

I'm so boooooooooooooooored!! T_T
I told Danny not to come over because I have to write an essay.... mou what a mistake T-T

Your Beauty lies in Plain Sight. Plain, simple and the girl next door. People tend overlook you as you are the "normal girl", but you're actually very beautiful. And you have plenty about you to set you apart, but more that lets you blend. People love the stability you have because as others may come and go, you will always be there and you may always be the same. You like simple things and that's what people like about you. You most likely enjoy things most consider normal, like movies, shopping, that sort of thing and are very friendly and probably have many friends. You are sweet and kind and that shows on you, but you're also strong and not very naive. You're a rather well-rounded individual. Even though some people pass you off as just another girl, shrug it off because they don't know what they're missing.</p><p align="center"><b>Some Things That Represent You:

You take the Stairway to Heaven.
Why stay down when you can go up? You, my ambitious friend, are going places, following your dreams. Good for you. Few people chase their dreams anymore. Never give that up. You are heading up in the world, making a name for yourself, even if it's just a small group who know it. You're finding your way and are heading straight for the top. You've got all the qualities of a great leader and are probably a very optimistic individual. Though you can be a bit selfish at times and have a tendency to step over people in your way. You must watch that. You could end up hurting the ones you love if you put your own goals above them. Never lose faith in that dream of yours, but make sure you can keep those close to you because in the end they'll be the ones to get you through the tough times. You have found your place and yourself, few can do so well and still struggle to find themselves. Don't let go of that sense of self you have even in times of confusion, it will help you pull through. Be careful of your ego too, you could lose your balances and once you're at the top, it's a very long way down. So be mindful of others, strive forward to reach your dream, whatever it may be, be true to yourself, and you keep going up. BTW many things have happened and I'm a happier bug >w<

So far spring break has been nice and relaxing.....and every morning my head feels like it weighs ten pounds more than it should...which is weird O_o...but once I'm actually up everything is ok! :D
Well I've got homework to do today... blah... along with a bunch of other chores and I still have to take the pups for a run :D

Anyways there's not much to report 'cept for the fun we've all been having with everyone down here.
Saturday we (Bri, Danny, Lizzy and Me) all played dart tag in my front yard :D 't was fun :D Danny fell and was hurt, but he's ok...ended up he only skinned his elbow and his knee. Which is good because it could have been a lot worse considering he tried to slide over my wall, but one of the bricks was loose, and he slipped and fell landing on the other little wall and then landing on the driveway >.o
but he's ok!
Sunday night  we (Bri, Danny, Rach and Me) played dart tag indoors because no one else was home and it was cold out side >.<
That was so much fun! My house was built to play dart tag! >w< muwahahaha!! one of these days I shall video tape our grand adventures >w< cause it's awesome >w<
Monday night, last night, we (Lizzy, Rach, Danny, and Me) played dart tag at Lizzy's park, aka Star Ridge Park, that was awesome! I'm such a happy hunter XD (who apparently has 1 new crush in Poway...according to the annoying advertisement to my right) anyways It was all great fununtil something started hunting us.
After that the game was called and we went back to Lizzy's house.... no one was in the mood to wrestle a coyote, mountain lion, or wolf.... or just be hunted by something that wasn't in the game in the first place.
Upon our return we discovered that Buddy, Lizzy's dog, had gotten into the chocolate chip cookies, that I'd made and brought ...and he'd eaten some of them. *sigh* oh well at least they're good enough to steal.
After that we all played Smash Brothers Brawl on the Wii and had lotsa laughs. We also played Wii bowling./..which I won, surprisingly...which was an unexpected upset, mainly because Danny was set to win with at that game.

Then we all went home...and slept....
which now brings you all the way to now... at which time I must say TTFN and dash away and run with my pups...and clean my dusty, dusty room >.o before doing other chores...all before 2:30 @-@
but hey I can do it because I'm me!

ja mata! *salutes*

<3

Well I've been away for a while... again >.o
School, work, and life have taken over time.

School has been evil.... My Tuesday/ Thursday classes are great, though there are a few issues with them. Like my lettering in Architecture... I'm sorry I have sloppy had writing, but at least I'm trying... And Drama...was well... that class cause me a minor break down...>.o You can only take so much "I don't know what you were doing, but that was crap" while in a class where you're really trying because you actually care about the class. In any case I'm doing far better in both classes now. I'm actually ahead of my arch class and I'm finally climbing the mountain of positives in my drama class.

Monday/Wednesday classes are a far different story. *stare of doom*
Mondays are filled with English, Trig and Poli. Sci. Wednesdays only have English and Trig.
Poli Sci is just boring because all my prof does is talk...and talk and talk and talk and talk.....
English. Well there has been a huge battle there regarding my grade....because it should be an "A" but the prof decided she wanted to be anal and actually count all the words on my first 2 essays...and then decided I didn't have enough words.  (I needed 1000 each). Once I fixed that problem I had an "A" on the first essay and a Zero on the second.
Yes.
That's right.
A Zero.
I snapped. I wanted to strangle this woman. And I probably would have ....but I still needed my grade. So I stayed after class and argued with her for about 20 minutes until I had to go to my next class. I'd planned on bombarding her with e-mails, but she e-mailed me first. Then there was a vollying of e-mails until this morning when i finally got her to take my essay and re-grade it after I got her to admit that she was wrong :D
Trig is another story. I'm averaging a "C" in that class right now.... and that's bad. Especially since I already took the class in HS. Why you ask am I averaging a "C"? well here is your answer: I am a slow test taker. I like to make sure I'm right. This is not possible with only 45 minutes to take the test. On the first test I scored a D+ ... I'd missed an entire page of problems.... had I actually seen and completed the page I'd've scored a B+.... -.-()   On the second test I scored an F+
Wow pretty sucky right? Granted I didn't really study too much for this test, however I didn't get to finish 5 problems.... which means I would've had a C+ on the test instead of an F+..... When I asked for more time on the next tests the response made me want to poke out one of his eyes. More time was not going to be given to me because I didn't have a note or a disability. I plan on yelling at him before our next test. I'm paying for the class. He's getting paid to teach the class. Therefore he orks for me. I will no longer be "requesting" more time. I'm demanding it. And as an educator he is required to give me more time... or I will take it to the dean.

oh yes I can be the student from hell... especially when I only need these classes because the previous ones that I've already taken don't count... or as far as my math class goes failing me for not showing all the work that I do in my head.... *eye twitch* (oh yes that happened. I tried to appeal the grade and got ignored.)

Anyways, more good things should be happening now days. Things are actually looking up and I think I might actually know what I want to do with my life now.
I'm going to major in Architecture and minor in drama and maybe music too ^_^
I have huge dreams and I plan on full-filling them...and surprisingly there's someone I never expected who completely supports me and wants me to reach my goals... o.o
I'm not really sure what to make of that just yet, but it can't be a bad thing. So I'm open to it ^-^

Anywhoo art has been slow, but I should be able to make up some time this next week since it's Spring Break!! whooo!!
Already??! but yeah it should be fun ^_^
I'm also hoping to catch up on the books that I had to put on hold. 2 of them I'm writing another I'm co-writing so I'm glad I finally have some down time to work on those and still have time to have some fun!!! >w<

well now I think I have some chores to do

Oh! the pups are both doing fine. Biggie had a few issues at the begining of the year but he's doing fine now, back in the house at nights too. ^_^ Maia is still as cute as ever and she's still a brat... basically she plays and gets excited when she wants to, not when you want her to XD

well that's all for now!
Later!

heh....
I think I got Danny and Bri mad at me.... it was kinda my fault but not at the same time. They pissed me off and I was having a bad week... (school started this week if you didn't know) I was stressed and then reminded of something painful that I didn't want to remember and that made me sad and mad all at the same time. You know the side of me that gets locked away for the safety of everyone was starting to come out.... I could see the eyes looking at me and I felt lost with in them.

I suppose I'm being over dramatic. In any case I'm pretty sure they're mad at me because I told them I couldn't hang out tonight because I have many things to do, namely homework. School has just begun again and I'm taking five classes for 14 units:D

Tuesdays and Thursdays I have Architecture from 9am-12:05 and then Drama from 2:25-4:30pm
whoooooooooooooooo!! (Wednesdays I only have English and trig)

So it's been a while... don't know how long, but it's been LONG!
Anyways there's been new developments down here. I had to get a job...o.o... so now on the weekends I will be refereeing for the PYBL! yay me! >w<
that should be fun ^_^ I was going to work at Ralph's with Briana and Daniel (do you know about Daniel? ponders* hmmm i don't think you do) but today I decided against it. Frankly working with them would be fun and all... but I might get distracted by them and that would be bad. I also might get overloaded...or smothered by them.... which would not only be bad it would be REALLY bad.... I like my friends and I would not want to spend nights and weekends alone just because I've seen them every other day >_<
So I'm going to work for my dad again (I was laid off, but now I am rehired! yay!) and once the season starts my weekends will be filled with basketball...and possibly angry parents wanting to jump me because of one bad call >.o

Oh yeah the reason I'm writing this! I almost forgot!
well! it's all because of Daniel, aka Dan/ Danny. He's my new friend! XD he's a crazy boy who I know through Bri... though come to think of it I think we hang out more than Bri and I do... O_o hmm...
anyways. We're pretty good friends and we like to have fun and stuff. He likes to let me beat him up and I enjoy that...I also enjoy poking him...because he's extra ticklish >w< muwahahaha! Also Rach can attest to this, we like to wrestle or as Bri says "wrastle" it's nothing really...besides fun. We just try and pin each other...constantly. Though I'm at a disadvantage since he was a wrestler in high school >.o but I win a few times :D I think the main reason I lose is because most of my power moves are for immobilizing my opponent... which i don't want to do to Danny since he's my friend and I could really hurt him O-O that would be bad.
but that's not the point of this confusion!
ha!
ok!
*ahem* since we are such good friends some people seem to have the idea that we may be a couple.... this is not true and I don't understand it!!! T_______T it wasn't so bad that Nicole (another person from Ralph's) thought we were together because umm... she's kinda umm... she's dumb...to put it nicely. So it wasn't bad and we all could ignore her (we being Danny, Bri and I)
however! apparently something happened and now Bri thinks there's something going on between us too!!! T__________________T
whyyyyyyyy???????????????????????? seriously! there's nothing going on between us! T-T
this whole situation is confusing and somewhat annoying.... if anyone would like to shed some light on this situation... by all means... please do.

anywhooo... umm I think that's all. Oh! I did a photo shoot! er my own photo shoot >w< I made Danny, Bri and Rach help me. Though Bri weaseled out of it  because ...well she didn't have a dress. She still helped. The entire photo shoot isn't finished yet, there are still a few scenes that need to be shot. We just lost our light and couldn't take anymore pics >.o so it shall be completed...at a later time, soon hopefully :D

well that's all for now!
Sorry I've been away for so long!

So southern Cali is on fire again. The fire's pretty much on the same path as the 03 Cedar fire was on. But instead of diverting north to Camp Pendleton this one has jumped the freeway and has pretty much made it's way to the ocean. fun fun fun
I haven't heard from my friends yet... I know they've been evacuated and its driving me crazy that they haven't called >_<

after that weekend most of them left. So it was just my granpa, grandma, the small one (Gabby), and my normal family members (mom, dad, and bro). I've been thinking a lot lately. Mainly because I haven't been writting as much as I used to, especially for my stories and stuff.
I've been thinking that maybe I was meant for war...and not this peace stuff (lounging around the house ect.)... I dunno I guess I'm sort of restless at heart. I want adventure. I want to see places I've never been...I want to fight (oh yes I've been itching to see if I could really knock someone out >w<) I want to be envolved... though anyone who knows me knows that I could never be in the armed forced... Ok...so i'd been doing fine for the last month or so...right? right. and then.... yesterday happened. Really long day of school... had to drop most of my classes and I'll probably end up just taking the semester off because it just doesn't seem worth it right now.

So I was incredibly tired since I started classes at 8am and ended at aout 5pm... So I came home really just wanting to collapse in front of my computer and talk with my friends who always have the power to lift my spirits. And wouldn't you know it...the bloody internet is down.

So I ask my mom what'up and apparently she KNEW it was down. Good God, woman! why didn't you do something about it when it FIRST went down??!!! So they made me call the stupid cox communications and by now I was in a mood... a very BAD mood.So I couldn't find the number and started slamming things around while looking for it. then my dad came up and yelled at me because I was slamming things.

Personally I had the right to be slamming things. The number wasn't where it was supposed to be, i was already tired and frusterated and the idiot operators didn't have the number. So I finally find get the phone number and the guy can't help me cause I can't move my mom's desks it's too bloody heavy. So he directsme someone else.... in Arizona... what heck?! the people in arizonacan't reallyhelp me too much now can they...seeing as I'm in CALIFORNIA....*eyetwitch* so the nice young lady gives me the CA number and then I dial and have to go through the annoying phone-number-button-push routine for the Nth time that night...and wouldn't you know it...I end up in Ohio. I mean COME ON!! how stupid is this?!! *flail* So anyways...the Ohio guy can help me...apparently and so he gets to work....ends up that they're just gonna send someone out to fix the problem.... tomorrow in the afternoon X_x *eyetwitch* So then I just handed the phone to my mom...to make sure that's ok...which is why I didn't want to handle the call in the first place... but apparently they're just too busy sleeping or watching the news to even carea bout my problems... no matter how big or small they may be. (the internet is working now...obviously)

So after that I kinda freaked out and broke down... I've been feeling rather worthless and incredibly neglected by my family lately....and my friends have always been able to cheer me up. Couldn't talk with my last night...the internet was down... I do REALLY stupid things when I'm angry and depressed.

Why am I feeling neglected and worthless? Because of my parents who apparently play favorites. I can have the best grades and have the abiliy to do what ever I want but I'll never be good enough to outshine my brother. Because he's perfect, remember? he has the most talent and he's gonna be a professional baseball player...if that is he can get his grades up.

So that's what this is about. I've lived in his shadow ever since I was six years old...the same time he could play baseball... ironically it's the same time I had to start wearing glasses... I've been ok with it...until now. Why? Because he did really bad with with his grades last semester...and now my parents are taking the school to court... because they didn't do anything. How come they didn't throw a fit when I had to sit the bench in Softball?I was one of the better players, so how come they didn't do anything? How come they didn't take the school to court when my couselor told me I couldn't do what I wanted to do and to pretty much give up any hope of ever doing it in the future? How come they didn't take the school to court when my Band teacher was pushing me down for not kissing his @$$ like all the other girls?

.....They keep telling me that I'll be great on my own and that I won't have to ride on anyone's coat tails.... but I already know that... But when they say it... it sounds like pure bull$#!+ because I don't believe them...I don't believe they care... their actions speak far louder than their words.... and I just can't believe them anymore. Blind naivete can only take someone so far... until the lies are just so blunt, that to say otherwise would be to point the finger at yourself...

I don't know...maybe it is my fault... but I don't really care anymore... That's why I'm so glad I'm going to Japan...I'll finally be free. They think that I'll cry and miss them and what not... but I won't shed a tear. I'll finally be free... if only for a little while...

~To my friends out there who read this... I love you guys with my heart and soul If anything happened to any one of you I don't know what I'd do. (er well if someone hurt you I'd go hunt them down and the beat the crap outta them, but that's for a different journal ^-^)~
